Title: 'Entrepreneurship '
DateModified: '2019-03-05'
DatePublished: '2019-03-05'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2019/applications/entrepreneurship
SetInCountry: India
Category: Making a local connection
AuthorName: Sunny Jayker
AuthorCountry: India
Text: "Sridhar Vembu\nCEO of Zoho Corp. (formerly AdventNet Inc.), the company behind\
  \ the Zoho suite of online applications.\n\nHe co-founded AdventNet in 1996, and\
  \ has been CEO since 2000. AdventNet has transformed itself from a modest beginning\
  \ as a software company serving network equipment vendors to a be an innovative\
  \ online applications provider.\n\nsuccess stories\n\nIt has maintained growth and\
  \ profitability, without needing outside capital. Prior to AdventNet, Sridhar worked\
  \ as a wireless systems engineer at Qualcomm, Inc. where he was fortunate to work\
  \ with some of the leading minds in wireless communications.\n\nSridhar Vembu\u2019\
  s Zoho competes successfully around the world with some core products of Microsoft,\
  \ Google and Salesforce.com. Vembu shuns outside capital, but if Zoho were to be\
  \ valued, it might be well over $1 billion.\n\nHe grew up in a very modest middle-class\
  \ family in Chennai. His father was a stenographer in the High Court. Neither his\
  \ father nor his mother went to college.\n\nHe went to a Tamil-medium, government-aided\
  \ school till Std 10, and then he did 11th and 12th in an English-medium government\
  \ school.\n\nHe did well at school and he obtained his Bachelor\u2019s degree in\
  \ Electrical Engineering from Indian Institute of Technology, Madras, and PhD in\
  \ Electrical Engineering from Princeton University."
